<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">WHAT I DID . . .</b></font> - <small>Aazen, Dark Elf Necromancer, Tunare</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    Well the post above mine, Tips, already covers some useful tactics, so I won't go in to that really.I plan to go into places and creatures.Once I hit level 8, I bought all of my spells immediately(duh).I fought for quite a few levels in the West Commonlands.Make sure to summon up a YELLOW pet, then find a young kodiak.The lowest one will con is yellow,(so be prepared for a good fight!), and they go up a very shallow red.YKs basically go from lvls 9-11.Anyhow, get your DOTs on the creature, jump into melee(letting your pet take most of the hits), when it is down pretty far, maybe 30% area, jump in and take hits for your pet.If you get down too low, lifespike the #&@! out of the thing.If you are a damned good necro, you can fight nothing but reds until level 9.I fought pretty much all YKs up until level 11, taking out the occasional wisp.Warning:Don't mess with these wisps unless you have a magical weapon, because your pet won't be able to harm it.Once I hit level 11 I headed over to Chessboard in ButcherBlock mountains.The majority of what you will be fighting are undead pawns(put that Ward Undead spell to good use and practice Evocation)The loot here is nothing but bonechips(yeah!), no money at all :(, and only the occasional rusty weapon.(Bleh!)Be careful, you WILL be KOS to about 97% of every NPC on this entire continent!I bought 40 of both food and water before I came to this place, lol.Anyhow, once I hit level 12, I went into Lavastorm.This is a great zone for loot, unfortunately, your most powerful DOT (Blood Boil, lvl 12) will be resisted by every creature here, so don't even try it. Phooei!.Fought mostly drakes at level 12.They are pretty easy.At level 13, fought drakes and any white or blue conning basilisks and Rock Dervishes.If you can(laugh) try and avoid the Fire Elementals here.I know its kinda hard considering that they make up 75% of the population of this zone and they all are badly afflicted by wanderlust(they almost never stay in one spot), but try.Why?Because even a blue one can be dangerous.First off, if any of its friends see you, they will instantly jump in.Secondly, they not only hit hard, but have a VERY nasty damage shield.Since we get the Cancel Magic spell at lvl 16, we pretty much just have to put up with it.Once, out of curiousity, I tanked for my pet for the whole fight against a low blue elemental.By the time the fight was over, my pet was down to 32%!So be careful with these guys.Same applies to fire imps.Everything else in this zone is non-aggressive.I fought here until I hit level 15 last night.Thinking of doing Dervs in RO until lvl 16.Levels 12-15 are pretty hard levels for us Necros.The pet at this level is ridiculously weak.Just stick it out and try and hit lvl 16 as fast as possible.

		
    </small></font></p>
    <p><small><font face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></small></td>
  </tr>
